# Vmware


Vmware is a virtualization software that is widely used to implement OS virtualization and plays an important part in the cloud architecture of certain cloud infrastructure. VMware is compatible with the x86 processors.

VMware products are available for free download  fromthe following link:
http://www.vmware.com/products/server/overview.html


The VMware desktop software runs on operating systems like Linux, Windows, Mac OS X etc. The VMware enterprise
software hypervisors, VMware ESX and VMware ESXi are bare metal embedded hypervisors that run directly on server
hardware and do not require any OS.


The VMware server is availabel in a number of variants and can be selected based on the requirements:

These are:
VMware Player: this can be used for running one or two virtual machines
VMware vSphere Hypervisor: this can be used for virtualizing on physical host
VMware vSphere: This one can be used for running more than 100 virtual machines with centralized management and
cloud scalability


We can see the comparison among the various VMware products in this link:
http://www.vmware.com/products/datacenter-virtualization/server/compare.html
